parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause the engine light to come on, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine light comes on
P2015 code
soft or spongy clutch pedal
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coolant system can cause the coolant level to drop, leading to engine damage and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant level drops
coolant light comes on
vehicle overheats
engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle response can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: Zero throttle response
vehicle hesitates or stalls
engine speed indicator shows idle speed for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure - Lag, Jolt, and Unintended Neutral Shift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lag or jolt when shifting, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded. Unintended shifting into neutral can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a lag or delay when shifting into gear
the engine revs before the transmission engages
the vehicle shakes or jerks abnormally
the vehicle revs loudly before shifting into the next gear
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle unexpectedly shifts into neutral while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Low Oil Level
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure due to low oil level can cause the vehicle to stall or die while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine slows down
the engine light flashes
and the vehicle dies; the vehicle stalls without warning; the vehicle makes a loud sound before stalling; white smoke emitting from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of an oil level warning light can lead to engine failure due to low oil level, causing the vehicle to stall or die while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: No warning lights or indicators before engine failure; no oil level warning light; sudden engine failure without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine fire can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: White smoke emitting from the engine compartment; loud sound before the vehicle stalls; vehicle becomes engulfed in flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel electrical connector can cause a range of issues, including airbag malfunction, non-functional horn, and loss of cruise control, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates
horn does not function
cruise control is inoperable
other steering wheel-mounted controls may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC and ABS systems can cause a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light
Electronic Stability Control light
Steering Wheel Fault warning light
and Check Engine light illuminate on the dashboard
accompanied by a fault description message "FAULT: ABS/ELECTRONIC STABILIZATION CONTROL".
